The article is a message from the White House Office of the Press Secretary, dated March 13, 2012. It discusses the continuation of the national emergency with respect to Iran. The President has sent a notice to the Federal Register stating that the emergency, which was declared on March 15, 1995, will continue beyond March 15, 2012. The letter explains that the crisis between the United States and Iran has not been resolved and that the actions and policies of the Iranian government are contrary to the interests of the United States. As a result, the President has determined that it is necessary to maintain comprehensive sanctions against Iran to address this threat. The letter is signed by President Barack Obama.